# Catalyst One Development Charter

Before implementing any feature:

1. **Reuse** existing components wherever possible.
2. **Do not duplicate** business logic — extend shared libs / SSOT helpers. **Permanent:** every enterprise metric has exactly one implementation (`enterprise-metric-single-implementation.mdc`); Mission Control, CHANAKYA, SARATHI, APIs, and AI must consume it.
3. **Maintain enterprise UI consistency** with the established design system and spacing.
4. Keep all components **modular and reusable**.
5. **Never hardcode** business values that belong in masters or configuration.
6. **Preserve backward compatibility** unless explicitly instructed otherwise.
7. **Follow** existing design language and spacing (no one-off visual systems).
8. Ensure **accessibility** and **responsive** behaviour.
9. **Optimize for performance** (avoid unnecessary re-renders, heavy lists without virtualisation when needed).
10. **Do not leave TODOs** or placeholder implementations in production code.
11. **Validate** TypeScript, ESLint, and Production Build before completion.
12. If a **better architecture** is discovered during implementation, **explain it in the Implementation Report before changing it**.

## Mandatory completion

After implementation, deliver the full **Implementation Report** (summary, components created/modified, DB/API/routes, business logic, UX, performance, compatibility, validation, Git, testing checklist, final status, recommendations) plus the Business & Functional Certification Report when in the certification environment.
